description: From Dutch kaketoe, borrowed from Malay kakaktua, kakatua. Spelling influenced by cock.

entries.meaning: A bird of the family Cacatuidae with a curved beak and a zygodactyl foot. [from 1610s]
examples: We saw some cockatoos in the aviary.

entries.meaning: (slang, obsolete) A lookout posted during a two-up game, when gambling was illegal.
